AGI -&nbsp;"I sent the Secretary General of the Farnesina to call the ambassador of the Russian Federation in Italy. The Government calls for clarification on the nationalization of the Ariston&nbsp; Thermo Group. At work also with Brussels, in connection with Germany". The Minister for Foreign Affairs, Antonio&nbsp;Tajani, >su X.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
After the decision of the Russian government to proceed to the temporary transfer of the Russian subsidiary of the Italian company &nbsp;Ariston&nbsp;Thermo Group, to the Russian Gazprom Household Systems Jsc, manufacturer of appliances that heads Gazprom, the Minister of Enterprises and Made in Italy, Adolfo Urso>, has had a telephone conversation with Paolo Merloni, > president of &nbsp; Ariston In the afternoon the minister Urso will meet in Pescara the president of the Marche Region, Francesco Acquaroli, in whose area of Fabriano the Italian multinational has the headquarters and operational.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
In a note, the Ariston Group is surprised by what happened. "The Ariston Group, which has been working industrially in the Russian Federation for almost 20 years with very correct relations with local institutions, has not been previously informed of the Decree and is extremely surprised by this initiative. With Decree 294 - it explains - the president Putin has placed the subsidiary Ariston Thermo Rus LLC under the temporary management of JSC Gazprom Household Systems, a company controlled by the Gazprom group. Waiting for explanations on the unexpected measure >, we are evaluating the implications, even from the point of view of governance and management. To date, the Ariston Group owns a production plant dedicated to water heating located outside St. Petersburg (with about 200 direct and indirect employees), which produces high-efficiency products for the internal market, a center of excellence for local product development and a Moscow business manager (which coordinates about 100 employees active also in the local business branches of the whole Federation), all operating under the renowned Ariston brand. The group generated approximately 100 million euros of turnover in the Russian Federation in the fiscal year 2023 and had a significant capital base to operate in the local market, result of almost two decades of investment". &nbsp;
